## F3 — LOW (slicer-readiness) — percentile research columns are heavily NaN

In `context_trades.csv`:
- `SignalKyleLambdaPctile` is NaN for 1397/3585 trades (39%).
- `SignalATRPctile` is NaN for 974/3585 trades (27%).

Not a correctness bug — NaN is honest. Cause: `rolling_percentile` (zscore.py:110)
uses a `window+1`(=21)-bar window stacked on top of the underlying indicator's own
warmup (ATR needs 14, Kyle lambda needs a 20-bar cov window), so the first valid
percentile lands well into the session. Consequence: any slice on these two
columns silently uses only the late-session subset of trades. Flagging now because
the user is about to declare slicer candidates — if either percentile column is a
candidate, its limited coverage should be a known input to that decision, not a
surprise discovered mid-slice.

